                                    "regulatoryAbstract": "This Medwatch Safety Alert informs that use of docetaxel drug may cause symptoms of alcohol intoxication. Docetaxel is a prescription chemotherapy drug used to treat different kinds of cancers. FDA is warning that docetaxel contains ethanol, also known as alcohol, which may cause patients to experience intoxication or feel drunk during and after treatment. FDA is revising the labels of all docetaxel drug products to warn about this risk. FDA recommends  Health care professionals to consider the alcohol content of docetaxel when prescribing the drug to patients, particularly in those whom alcohol intake should be avoided or minimized and when using it in conjunction with other medications.",
